<b>Symptoms</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The pain is usually mild, but as this is also a chronic disease it can be intense. This is a type of headache that causes throbbing pain on one or both sides of your head, unlike migraine. It also doesn't share the same symptoms as that of migraine such as nausea and vomiting. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">

</span>
